      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "I'M EASY (6) trailed the lead and fought on well to be beaten 2 lengths into second (24.17) at Traralgon in a Grade 5 over 425m. Sure to be about the mark. SHOW BOAT JOHNNY (7) turned in a solid run last start over 350m at this track finishing 4th and beaten only half a length (19.72). Solid record here at the distance winning three races. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from four starts. Worth another chance. KING BRUNO (2) was in the minors two back (23.11) at Geelong but ran below best last time there, finishing 8th. The form out of last race has been strong. Key runner who gets his chance to atone. SUMMER HAIL (1) missed the placings here last start but is well-placed to make amends.",
